What is an RTD // insert RTD picture
A Resistance Temperature Dectector (RTD) is a sensor whose resistance changes as its temperature changes. The RTD we will be using today is the PT100, from hardware company, Adafruit. The PT indicates that the &ldquo;resistor&rdquo; inside is just a small strip of platinum, and the 100 indicates at 0 degrees celsius the platinum will have a resistance of 100 Ohms.
